{"lemma":"رَجْعَةٌ","slug":"رَجْعَةٌ","root":"ر.ج.ع","root_slug":"ر-ج-ع","root_link":"/words/roots/ر-ج-ع","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":false},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n14890","n14914"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B1%D9%8E%D8%AC%D9%92%D8%B9%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":null,"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n14890","headword_ar":"رَجْعَةٌ","root":"rjE","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"inf. n. of un. of 1;"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A return; a single act of returning, of going back, coming back,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"reverting:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) [and]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rujuwEN","text_ar":"رُجُوعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e. the act of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"returning,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c. (Msb.) ―         -b2-  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"returning to the present state of existence"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"after death."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K.) So in the phrase,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN yuw^ominu","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ يُوْمِنُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biAlr~ajoEapi","text_ar":"بِالرَّجْعَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one believes in the returning to the present state of existence after death"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S, Msb, K. *) This was a tenet of some of the Arabs in the Time of Ignorance, and of a sect of Muslim innovators, and of a sect of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raAfiDap","text_ar":"رَافِضَة"},{"kind":"text","text":", who say that 'Alee the son of Aboo-Tálib is concealing himself in the clouds, to come forth when he shall be summoned to do so. (L.) ―         -b3-  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"returning,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"homeward course, of a military expedition;"},{"kind":"text","text":"opposed to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"badoA^apN","text_ar":"بَدْاَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", q. v. (T and Mgh in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bdA^","text_ar":"بدا"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b4-  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"return of a party of warriors to war after their having come back from an expedition."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b5-  Also, and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rijoEapN","text_ar":"رِجْعَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, A, Nh, Mgh, Msb, K,) but the former is the more chaste, (S, Msb, TA,) though the latter is mentioned before the former in the K, (TA,) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A man's returning to his wife,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"restoring her to himself,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"taking her back by marriage"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to the marriage-state, after having divorced her;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IF, Msb;) the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"returning of the divorcer to the divorced woman:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"taking back to marriage a woman who has been divorced, but not by an absolutely-separating sentence, without a new contract."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Nh.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lahu EalaY A@moraA^atihi","text_ar":"لَهُ عَلَى ا@مْرَاَتِهِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajoEapN","text_ar":"رَجْعَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rijoEapN","text_ar":"رِجْعَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He has a right of returning to,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"taking back, his wife after having divorced her"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (S, Mgh:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yamoliku Alr~ajoEapa EalaY zawojatihi","text_ar":"يَمْلِكُ الرَّجْعَةَ عَلَى زَوْجَتِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He possesses the right of returning"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]: (Msb:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tal~aqa fulaAnN fulaAnapa TalaAqFA yamoliku fiyhi Alr~ajoEapa","text_ar":"طَلَّقَ فُلَانٌ فُلَانَةَ طَلَاقًا يَمْلِكُ فِيهِ الرَّجْعَةَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a man divorced such a woman by a divorce in which he possessed the right of returning"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]. (TA.) ―         -b6-  Also the former, (S, Msb, TA,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rijoEapN","text_ar":"رِجْعَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"likewise, (Msb,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rujoEapN","text_ar":"رُجْعَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rujoEaY","text_ar":"رُجْعَى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[which is originally an inf. n.] and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rujoEaAnN","text_ar":"رُجْعَانٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[which is also originally an inf. n.] and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"marojuwEN","text_ar":"مَرْجُوعٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"marojuwEapN","text_ar":"مَرْجُوعَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajuwEapN","text_ar":"رَجُوعَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajoEN","text_ar":"رَجْعٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) the last of these is allowable, (TA,) [being an inf. n. used in the sense of a pass. part. n.,] (tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"reply,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"answer,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of an epistle. (S, Msb, * K, TA.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"halo jaA='a","text_ar":"هَلْ جَا=ءَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajoEapu kitaAbika","text_ar":"رَجْعَةُ كِتَابِكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rujoEaAnuhu","text_ar":"رُجْعَانُهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Hath the reply,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"answer, of thine epistle come:?"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^arosaltu A_ilayoka famaA jaA='aniY rujoEaY","text_ar":"اَرْسَلتُ اـِلَيْكَ فَمَا جَا=ءَنِى رُجْعَى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"risaAlatiY","text_ar":"رِسَالَتِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I sent to thee, and the reply,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"answer, of my epistle came not to me;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e. ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"marojuwEuhaA","text_ar":"مَرْجُوعُهَا","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, K, * TA:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnK Ealayoka","text_ar":"فُلَانٍ عَلَيْكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA kaAna mino marojuwEi","text_ar":"مَا كَانَ مِنْ مَرْجُوعِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"What was"},{"kind":"text","text":"[the purport]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the reply,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"answer, of such a one to thee?"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA.) And [in like manner]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alr~i$oq","text_ar":"الرِّشْق"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajoEu","text_ar":"رَجْعُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"What is returned against,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in opposition to,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in reply to,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the simultaneous discharge of a number of arrows in a particular direction."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b7-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rijoEapN","text_ar":"رِجْعَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["TA","S","Msb","K","A","Nh","Mgh"]},{"entry_id":"n14914","headword_ar":"رَجْعَةٌ","root":"rjf","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zalozalapN","text_ar":"زَلْزَلَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K) [meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Commotion, agitation,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"convulsion;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"violent commotion"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.; and particularly"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an earthquake;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a violent earthquake:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a vehement cry from heaven:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Jel in vii. 76:) or it signifies, in the Kur-án,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"any punishment that befalls a people."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, O.)"}],"source_refs":["S","K"]}]},"classical_definitions":{"source":"hawramani","url":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/%D8%B1%D8%AC%D8%B9%D8%A9/","headword_ar":"رجعة","entries":[{"lexicon_id":"dictionary_18","lexicon_en":"Al-Sharīf al-Jurjānī, Kitāb al-Taʿrīfāt (d. 1413 CE)","lexicon_ar":"كتاب التعريفات للشريف الجرجاني","permalink":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/?p=23275#a22cfd","body_html":"<span>الرجعة في الطلاق: هي استدامة القائم في العدة، وهو ملك النكاح.</span>"}]}}